Role of FNP GitHub support team:

- Github technical support for nerds and teachers
- Manage version control permissions
- Trimming low signal content over time
- Editing/ Updating content (new lessons, L2 & L3 additions)


-------> Pod welcome video

Purpose: to personally welcome new foot nerds, thank them for the commitment, provide key information about program

Components:
[Nick]
- Welcome to your foot nerd journey
- Thank you for being here. Thank you for making a commitment to spend 1 hour a day on your health
- Your journey officially kicks off on Feb 1st with Block 1

[Ruth]
- Your pod is your immediate community within the foot nerd tribe. Your family for the next 360 days
- Learning partners have been assigned by student number. If you wish to change partners please do so within the first week of the program

[Nick]
- Slack is our primary communication platform within the Nerd community. It's our conference center in cyberspace where we connect with each other
- Channel = individual room in the center, create a channel if you want to open a discussion about a topic, DM others to keep channels clear

- Dialogue covenant: A very important document. Our rules of engagement when it comes to dialoge. 
- Facilitates beautiful disagreements that lead us to truth. Every Nerd understands it and holds themselves to it. Rules instead of rulers
- Constantly evolving, please send us feedback if you have any
- Please read it before starting the program. Link to the file is in your Block 1 PDF

[Ruth]
- Individual welcomes: Name, home city, mention a part of their application

[Nick]
- Using the framework to guide your personalized journey 

[Ruth]
- Flexible design: what you get out of the program is up to you

[Nick]
- Be inspired by each other, engage in dialogue, share your stories to help inspire others

[Nick]
- Success: spend a deliberate hour each day on your health (you define what that means, we are here to share our perspective)

[Ruth]
- Engaging with your pod, your partner and the global nerd tribe Slack is a powerful community element

Wishing y'all a fun learning journey. Send us a message on Slack if you have questions

